#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:1
msgid "Numark NS4FX"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:4
msgid "[Manufacturer’s product page](https://www.numark.com/product/ns4fx)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:5
msgid ""
"[Forum thread](https://mixxx.discourse.group/t/numark-ns4-fx-mapping-"
"repository/32767)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:7
msgid ""
"The Numark NS4FX is a 4 channel (with channel layering) DJ controller with "
"an integrated audio interface. Its stand out feature is the LCD displays "
"integrated into the jog wheels. It is a USB Audio and MIDI Class compliant "
"device and works with Linux, macOS, and Windows."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:13
msgid "Audio interface"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:16
msgid ""
"Configure Mixxx’s main output for channels 1-2 and Headphones output for "
"Channels 3-4."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:18
msgid ""
"The microphone input on this controller is not available to the computer "
"through the controller’s audio interface. It is mixed with the main output "
"in hardware, so this controller’s audio interface is not suitable for "
"broadcasting or recording the inputs. If you want to use the controller for "
"broadcasting or recording, a separate {ref}`audio interface <hardware-audio-"
"interfaces>` with a microphone input is suggested."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:22
msgid "Configuration Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:25
msgid "You can set configuration options in the Mixxx controller preferences."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:27
msgid ""
"**Enable Wheel on startup** When enabled (default), the jog wheels will be "
"in vinyl/scratch mode by default. When disabled, they will be in pitch "
"bend/nudge mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:29
msgid ""
"**SHIFT + Load ejects track** When enabled (default), holding the SHIFT "
"button and pressing LOAD will eject the track from the deck. If disabled, it"
" will load and play the selected track."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:31
msgid ""
"**Use effect only on active deck** When enabled, effects are only applied to"
" the currently active deck (e.g., Deck 1 or 3). When disabled (default), "
"effects are applied to both decks on that side (e.g., Deck 1 and 3)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:33
msgid ""
"**Display VU from both decks** When enabled, the channel VU meters will "
"display the left and right master output levels. When disabled (default), "
"they will display the individual level for each active deck. **Select "
"default pad mode after Mixxx startup** Sets the performance pad mode that is"
" active when Mixxx starts. **Control stems with Fader Cuts pads** When "
"enabled, the 'Fader Cuts' pad mode is replaced with a mode to control Stems "
"(mute, volume and quick effects). **Add hotcues 5-8 to the second row of "
"pads** When enabled, the bottom row of transport pads (CUE, START, BACK, "
"FWD) will function as hotcues 5-8 when the pad mode is set to 'Hot Cue'. "
"**Exit slip mode after scratching** When enabled, then when the slip mode is"
" on and you start scratching, the slip mode exits after you finish the "
"scratching so that the track can continue playing from the position where it"
" originally should have been."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:40
msgid "Mapping"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:43
#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:48
msgid "Numark NS4FX (schematic view)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:51
msgid ""
"**Browse Knob:** Rotate this knob clockwise to scroll down, counter "
"clockwise to scroll up. Press the Knob to load tracks into the inactive "
"deck, expand entries in the library view, and select playlists and crates. "
"**SHIFT + Turn:** Page down/page up, allows you to scroll by page instead of"
" by item. **SHIFT + Push:** Focus next library pane, allows you to toggle "
"between the left and right panes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:56
msgid ""
"**Load:** Press one of these buttons while a track is selected in the "
"library window to assign it to the active deck. **SHIFT + Load:** Load the "
"track and play. If the 'SHIFT + Load ejects track' option is set, eject the "
"track)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:59
msgid ""
"**Level:** Adjusts the pre-fader, pre-EQ audio level of the corresponding "
"channel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:61
msgid ""
"**Treble EQ:** Controls the treble frequencies for the individual channels."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:63
msgid ""
"**Mid EQ:** Controls the mid-range frequencies for the individual channels."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:65
msgid ""
"**Bass EQ:** Controls the bass frequencies for the individual channels."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:67
msgid ""
"**Filter:** Adjusts the amount of the filter effect. Turning the knob left "
"and right will produce a low-pass filter and high-pass filter, respectively."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:70
msgid ""
"**Headphone Cue:** Sends pre-fader audio to the cue channel for headphone "
"monitoring."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:72
msgid ""
"**Channel Fader:** Adjusts the volume of the individual channels in the "
"software."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:74
msgid ""
"**Main Output LEDs:** Displays the audio level going to the Main Output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:76
msgid "**Crossfader:** Controls the blend between the two decks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:78
msgid "**Cue Gain:** Adjusts the volume for headphone cueing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:80
msgid ""
"**Cue Mix:**; Adjusts the audio output to the headphones, mixing between the"
" cue output and the master mix output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:82
msgid ""
"**FX Wet/Dry Knob:** Turn this knob to adjust the wet/dry mix of the "
"effects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:84
msgid ""
"**Beats Multiplier:** As Mixxx does not have a single BEATS knob, you can "
"use it to control the **effect units' Super knobs**. **SHIFT + Turn** "
"controls **main mix** gain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:87
msgid ""
"**Tap BPM:** Press this button 4 or more times to manually enter a new BPM. "
"The software will ignore the track's BPM and follow your manually entered "
"tempo."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:90
msgid ""
"Press SHIFT and this button to reset the tempo to the track’s default BPM."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:92
msgid ""
"**Software FX:** Press one or more of these buttons to select active "
"software effects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:94
msgid ""
"**FX On / Off / Hold:** Push up on the toggle switch to latch (lock) the FX "
"in the 'on' position. Push down on the toggle switch to turn the FX on "
"momentarily. When the toggle switch is in the middle position, the FX will "
"be off."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:98
msgid ""
"**Layer:** Press this button to select which layer in the software is "
"controlled by that hardware deck. Deck A can control Layer 1 or 3 while Deck"
" B can control Layer 2 or 4."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:101
msgid ""
"**Platter/Jog Wheel:** This capacitive, touch-sensitive jog wheel controls "
"the audio when the wheel is touched and moved. When the Scratch button is "
"not active, use the jog wheel to bend the pitch of the track. When the "
"Scratch button is active, use the jog wheel to grab and move the audio, "
"\"scratching\" the track as you would with a vinyl record. You can also grab"
" the non-touch-sensitive outer wheel to bend the pitch of the track."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:106
msgid ""
"Press SHIFT and move the wheel to quickly search through the track audio."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:108
msgid ""
"**Display:** Use this screen to view information about the current track. "
"See the TODO DISPLAY for more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:111
msgid ""
"**SHIFT:** Allows multiple control commands to be triggered when pressed "
"first along with other buttons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:113
msgid ""
"**Scratch:** Press this button to turn on the scratch feature for the jog "
"wheel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:115
msgid ""
"**Pitch Fader:** Adjust the speed of the music. Moving towards the \" + \" "
"will speed the music up, while moving towards the \"–\" will slow it down. "
"**NOTE:** You can reverse the slider direction by deactivating the `Down "
"increases speed` option in Mixxx Deck preferences. **SHIFT + Pitch Fader** "
"changes the pitch range of the deck between 4% to 90%."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:122
msgid ""
"**Pitch Bend Down:** Press and hold to momentarily reduce the speed of the "
"track. **SHIFT + Pitch Bend Down:** Adjust the key of the playing track "
"down. **Pitch Bend Up + Pitch Bend Down:** Toggle keylock."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:126
msgid ""
"**Pitch Bend Up:** Press and hold to momentarily increase the speed of the "
"track. **SHIFT + Pitch Bend Up:** Adjust the key of the playing track up. "
"**Pitch Bend Up + Pitch Bend Down:** Toggle keylock."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:130
msgid ""
"**Sync:** Set the BPM of this deck to match the opposite deck. **Press:** "
"Press once to synchronize the tempo (BPM) to that of to that of the other "
"track **Long Press:** Enable {ref}`Sync Lock <sync-lock>`. Press again to "
"disable. **SHIFT + Sync:** Toggle quantize mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:135
msgid ""
"**Cue (Transport Control):** Behavior depends on the {ref}`cue mode "
"<interface-cue-modes>` set in the Mixxx preferences. **SHIFT + Cue:** return"
" the play head to the start of the track and stop the deck."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:138
msgid ""
"**Play/Pause:** Starts and suspends playback. **SHIFT + Play:** Toggles slip"
" (roll) mode for the current deck."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:141
msgid ""
"**Performance Pads:** These pads have different functions on each deck "
"depending on the current pad mode. See {ref}`performance-pads` for more "
"information to learn how to use the pads in each mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:144
msgid ""
"With Mixxx, the bottom row of pads is used to trigger Stutter, Start, Search"
" Backward and Search Forward:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:146
msgid ""
"**Stutter:** Repeats or \"stutters\" the sample when the pad is repeatedly "
"tapped from the last cue position."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:147
msgid "**Start:** Jumps to the beginning of the current track."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:148
msgid "**Search Backward:** Searches backward through the current track."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:149
msgid "**Search Forward:** Searches forward through the current track."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:151
msgid "TIP: the bottom four pads can also be used for the selected pad mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:153
msgid "**Cue mode:** Press this button to enter Cue mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:155
msgid "**Auto Loop:** Press this button to enter Auto Loop mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:157
msgid "**Fader Cuts:** Press this button to enter Fader Cuts mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:159
msgid "**Sampler:** Press this button to enter Sampler mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:161
msgid ""
"**Loop On/Off:** Press this button to activate auto loop on/off. Hold SHIFT "
"and press this button to trigger a reloop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:163
msgid ""
"**Loop 1/2:** Press this button when a loop is active to decrease the loop "
"size by half. Hold SHIFT and press this button to set the Loop In point."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:165
msgid ""
"**Loop x2:** Press this button when a loop is active to double the loop "
"size. Hold SHIFT and press this button to set the Loop Out point."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:167
msgid ""
"**Mic 1/Line Switch:** Flip this switch to the appropriate position, "
"depending on the device connected to the Mic 1 Input. If you are using a "
"microphone connected to the Mic 1 Input, set the switch to Mic 1. If you are"
" using a device such as a CD player or sampler connected to the AUX input, "
"set the switch to Line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:170
msgid ""
"**Mic 1/Line Level:** Turn this knob to adjust the level for the Mic 1 Input"
" or Aux Input."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:172
msgid ""
"**Mic 1/Line Tone:** Turn this knob to adjust the tone of the Mic 1 Input or"
" Aux Input. Turn left to increase the Low frequency tone, or turn right to "
"increase the High frequency tone."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:175
msgid ""
"**Booth Volume:** Turn this knob to adjust the output volume of the Booth "
"Output mix."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:177
msgid ""
"**Main Volume:** Turn this knob to adjust the output volume of the Main "
"Output mix."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:181
msgid "Performance Pads:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:184
msgid ""
"The top row of pads 31-34 controls hotcues, loops, stems and samples "
"function of the performance pads below. To select a mode, just press one of "
"these upper pads. An LED under the pad section indicates the currently "
"selected mode. See the subsections below for details about each mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:189
msgid "Cue Mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:192
msgid ""
"Press the **CUE** pad (31) to enter the cue mode. By pressing a pad from the"
" upper row of performance pads, you assign a hotcue 1-4 at the current play "
"position of the track. The assigned pad will be illuminated. If that pad was"
" already assigned a hotcue, the deck starts to play the current track from "
"the hotcue-assigned position. To erase a hotcue, press SHIFT + pad related "
"to that hotcue."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:198
msgid ""
"**TIP:** If you enable the 'Add hotcues 5-8 to the second row of pads' "
"option in the controller's preferences, you add another row of hotcues 5-8."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:200
msgid "Auto Loop Mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:203
msgid ""
"Press the **AUTO LOOP** pad (32) to enter the auto loop mode. It assigns the"
" upper 4 performance pads to the following functions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:206
msgid "**Auto 1:** – Sets and starts playback of a 2-beat autoloop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:207
msgid "**Auto 2:** – Sets and starts playback of a 4-beat autoloop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:208
msgid "**Auto 3:** – Sets and starts playback of a 8-beat autoloop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:209
msgid "**Auto 4:** – Sets and starts playback of a 16-beat autoloop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:211
msgid ""
"**TIP:** You can also control loop s with the 'Loop On/Off', 'Loop 1/2' and "
"'Loop x2' buttons (35-37)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:213
msgid "Fader Cuts Mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:216
msgid ""
"Press the **FADER CUTS** pad (33) to enter the fader cuts mode. In Fader "
"Cuts mode, the pads will mute and unmute the deck’s audio signal in a way "
"that emulates crossfader movements toward that deck."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:219
msgid "Stems Mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:222
msgid ""
"*Stems* control separated drum (pad 1), bass (pad 2), melody (pad3) and "
"voice (pad 4) streams of a track. To activated stem control mode, activate "
"the 'Control stems with Fader Cuts pads' option in the Mixxx preferences of "
"your controller. Because stems replace Fader Cuts functionality, press the "
"**FADER CUTS** pad (33) to enter the stem mode afterwards."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:226
msgid ""
"**Toggle a stem** by pressing the corresponding stem pad 1-4 from "
"performance pads."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:227
msgid ""
"**Set a stem's volume** by holding a stem pad while rotating the BEATS knob "
"(15) left or right."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:228
msgid ""
"**Toggle a stem's effect** by holding SHIFT (22) while pressing the "
"corresponding stem pad."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:229
msgid ""
"**Set a stem's effect volume** by holding a stem pad, pressing SHIFT (22) "
"while rotating the BEATS knob (15) left or right."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:231
msgid "Sampler Mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:234
msgid ""
"Press the **SAMPLE** pad (34) to enter the sampler mode. A press of any of "
"the sample buttons 1-4 will load and start playing a sample if the sampler "
"is not loaded. Pressing the same pad again will start playing the sample "
"from its beginning. SHIFT + sample pad will stop playing the sample and "
"unloads it if it is not playing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:239
msgid ""
"Use **SHIFT + Cue Gain** (12) to adjust the volume of the sampler. When "
"switching to the pad mode to sampler, hold down SHIFT to control slots 5-8 "
"using the hotcue buttons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:241
msgid ""
"**Note:** The sampler pads on both the left and right decks control the same"
" sampler slots in Mixxx. This is a hardware limitation, as the controller "
"sends identical MIDI signals from both sides, preventing Mixxx from "
"distinguishing between them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:247
msgid "Jog Wheel display"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:250
msgid ""
"The Jog wheel of Numark NS4FX include a color LED display with useful "
"information about the loaded / playing track."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:252
#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:258
msgid "Numark NS4FX jog wheel display (schematic view)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:261
msgid "Active Deck: Indicates the currently active deck."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:263
msgid "Platter Position: Displays the current track position."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:265
msgid "BPM: Displays the current BPM for the selected track."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:267
msgid ""
"Keylock: This icon illuminates when Keylock is active for the current deck."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:269
msgid "Pitch Range: Shows the current pitch range."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:271
msgid "Pitch: Shows current pitch of the track."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:273
msgid ""
"Pitch Adjust: Indicates the direction to move the Pitch Fader to match the "
"current track’s BPM with the track on the opposite deck."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:275
msgid ""
"Time Remaining: Displays the time elapsed or time remaining for the current "
"track."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_ns4fx.md:277
msgid ""
"Time Bars: Provides visual reference to time remaining on the selected song."
" When the song is almost over these segments will flash to give a warning."
msgstr ""
